    <h2 class="text-4xl text-primary font-extrabold font-mono">What it's all about</h2>
    <div class="prose prose-xl max-w-full mt-12">
      Scientific knowledge and debates lie at the core of modern human societies. We need open, federated and self-hosted digital infrastructure to push the boundaries of open access, distribution and discussions in science. <br />
      In times of misinformation, fake news and political propaganda, science labour must be freed from corporate monopolies. Scientists, researchers, academics and their related organizations must have controls over the medium where their work is published, reviewed, shared, read and discussed. <br />
      The OpenScience Network is committed to develop open digital spaces that reflects the most urgent priorities in open science communities.<br />
      By leveraging upon a federated digital space, communities will be able to draft papers, browse contextual articles, engage in meaningful discussions and collaborate with other scientists without being siloed in walled garden or engaged in dark patterns.
